<p>Policing has become â€¦
â€œ</p>

<p>Maybe Iâ€™ll settle on something; maybe Iâ€™ll draw a blank and come back to it later. Often, if I sleep on it, a good idea will come to me. So if I get bogged down or blocked, I move on to the next sentence and come back to this one later.Â </p>

<p>In the end, maybe I come up with something like this. (Or, hopefully, by putting more time into it, something better than this.)</p>

<p>â€œYou havenâ€™t cured cancer or calculated pi to 1,000 decimal places, so what makes you think you can commit the perfect murder? Are you smarter than the cops? They can track you by the smallest thread from your coat; they can nab your DNA from a flake of skin and, ten minutes later, be beating down your door. Can avoid all those security cameras, the ones propped on mantlepieces, hidden inside teddy bears, tucked inside innocuous-looking picture frames? Murder is not a game for the average dummyâ€“or even the average smarty.â€</p>

<p>Remember to read everything you write out loud! You will hear problems more easily than you will see them.Â </p>

